pect to glisten ?\n\n- Sham\n|\nProfits don't always prove that you're doing it, passion does.\n\n- Goitsemang\n|\nSure, at some level scientists know nanobots will destroy mankind. They just can't resist seeing how it happens.\n\n- Cracked.com, You Might Be a Zombie and Other Bad News\n|\nIf You Respect Their Preparation,You never Drop the Baton\n\n- Vineet\n|\nWhat will has caused, will must be brought to correct.\n\n- Jocelyn Gibb, Light on C. S. Lewis\n|\nWe have our stories, and we speak of them, and weave them into other people's stories - that's how it goes, does it not?\n\n- Susan\n|\nCan you not see that women could do and would do a hundred times more for the slave, if she were not fettered?\n\n- Angelina\n|\nMy mom's one of 13 siblings, and they all got six kids, and till I was 13 everybody was in Compton.\n\n- Kendrick\n|\nYet for my part, deeply as I am moved by the religious architecture of the Middle Ages, I cannot honestly say that I ever felt the slightest emotion in any modern Gothic church.\n\n- Goldwin\n|\nBy fire, fever, storm and sword, your blood shall suffer this bane. No peace or joy for Wintersloe's lord, till the puzzle ring is whole again\n\n- Kate Forsyth, The Puzzle Ring\n|\nHe looked as if he had been poured into his clothes and had forgotten to say 'when.'\n\n- P.\n|\nYou have more power than you know, Samantha. You just have to be brave enough to realize it.\n\n- Adriana Mather, How to Hang a Witch\n|\nLook, do you see that poem?' she said suddenly, pointing.\n\n- L.M. Montgomery, Anne of Avonlea\n|\nIt is the community that suffers when it refuses to validate any outside standards, and won't allow even the legitimate exercise of authority by the professionals it has hired.\n\n- Kathleen Norris, Dakota: A Spiritual Geography\n|\nLife is a river,' a wise friend told me. 'It's flowing. You're never at the same place twice.\n\n- Kamal Ravikant, Live Your Truth\n|\nMeanings are not determined by situations, but we determine ourselves by 